  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then boil half a kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> butternut squash cubes</strong> to a baking tray with <strong>half </strong>of<strong> </strong>the <strong>garam masala </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray into the oven for 18-20 min or until the squash is tender with a slight bite – this is your <strong>roasted butternut squash</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668446703092-x200.jpg",
